### 1. Create a new Plane (POST)
# Expected: 201 Created
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "planeBrand": "Airbus",
  "planeModel": "A400",
  "manufacturingYear": 2013
}

### 2. Get all Planes (GET)
# Expected: 200 OK (List of planes)
# Or 204 No Content if the list is empty
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane

### 3. Get Plane by ID (GET)
# Replace '1' with the actual ID returned in step 1.
# Expected: 200 OK or 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/1

### 4. Update Plane (PUT)
# We update ONLY the model and year. "planeBrand" is null (not sent).
# Expected: 200 OK
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/6
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "planeModel": "A400neo",
  "manufacturingYear": 2023
}

### 5. Verify Update (GET)
# Check if model/year changed BUT "planeBrand" remains "Airbus".
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/1

### 6. Test Error: Update Non-Existent Plane (PUT)
# Try updating a plane ID that doesn't exist (e.g., 999).
# Expected: 400 Bad Request (based on your controller's catch block)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "planeBrand": "Boeing",
  "planeModel": "737"
}

### 7. Delete Plane (DELETE)
# Expected: 204 No Content
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/1

### 8. Verify Deletion (GET)
# Expected: 404 Not Found
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/plane/1